<PageMeta category="Engagement" variant="brand" updated="Updated 2026-05-14" damaKa={["Data Governance"]} />

      <h1>DPMSG working groups</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The Digital Property Market Steering Group does its substantive work through
        six working groups. OPDA leads or co-leads four of them. Each group has a
        remit and a folder of materials in the archive.
      </p>

      <Diagram caption="Six DPMSG working groups feed Steering. OPDA-led groups are highlighted in the table below.">
flowchart TB
  SG["`Steering Group
monthly governance`"]:::infra
  CP["`Comms & PR
Working Group`"]:::process
  EN["`Engagement
Working Group`"]:::process
  PO["`Policy
Working Group`"]:::process
  RE["`Regulator
Working Group`"]:::process
  TE["`Technical
Working Group`"]:::process

  SG --> CP
  SG --> EN
  SG --> PO
  SG --> RE
  SG --> TE
</Diagram>

      <h2 id="sixGroups">The six groups</h2>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Group</th><th>Remit</th><th>OPDA role</th><th>Materials</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Steering</strong></td>
            <td>Governance body — meets monthly, takes formal decisions, allocates work to the other five groups.</td>
            <td>OPDA Chair (Maria Harris) sits on it.</td>
            <td><a class="resource-link" href="/library/resources#cat-governance-bodies"><code>steering-group/materials/</code></a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Comms &amp; PR</strong></td>
            <td>External narrative, press, member-facing communications, Smart Data report contributions.</td>
            <td>OPDA-led. Output includes the DPMSG Data Standards Interoperability Spring 2025 report.</td>
            <td><a class="resource-link" href="/library/resources#cat-governance-bodies"><code>working-groups/comms-pr/</code></a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Engagement</strong></td>
            <td>Stakeholder management — members, government, industry. Runs the monthly all-member update.</td>
            <td>OPDA-led. Produces the monthly all-member update slide decks.</td>
            <td><a class="resource-link" href="/library/resources#cat-governance-bodies"><code>working-groups/engagement/</code></a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Policy</strong></td>
            <td>Public-policy positioning — DMCC implementation, MHCLG consultation responses, Smart Data Scheme design submissions.</td>
            <td>OPDA contributes; chaired in rotation.</td>
            <td><a class="resource-link" href="/library/resources#cat-governance-bodies"><code>working-groups/policy/</code></a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Regulator</strong></td>
            <td>Engagement with regulators — FCA, ICO, NTSELAT (and its successor), CLC, SRA, RICS, CILEx Regulation.</td>
            <td>OPDA participates; CLC takes the lead given its sandbox role.</td>
            <td><a class="resource-link" href="/library/resources#cat-governance-bodies"><code>working-groups/regulator/</code></a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Technical</strong></td>
            <td>The substantive standards work — schemas, OpenAPI, accreditation criteria, conformance test suites.</td>
            <td>OPDA-led. Owns the <code>@pdtf/schemas</code> package and the trust-framework spec repo.</td>
            <td><a class="resource-link" href="/library/resources#cat-governance-bodies"><code>working-groups/technical/</code></a></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 id="output">Notable working-group output</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Comms &amp; PR:</strong>
          <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/04-governance-bodies/working-groups/comms-pr/DPMSG-Data-Standards-Interoperability-Report-Spring-2025-FINAL-1-1.pdf"><code>DPMSG Data Standards Interoperability Spring 2025 Report</code></a> — the most cited public output of the DPMSG to date.</li>
        <li><strong>Comms &amp; PR:</strong>
          <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/04-governance-bodies/working-groups/comms-pr/data_standards_for_smart_data.pdf"><code>data_standards_for_smart_data.pdf</code></a> — companion explainer.</li>
        <li><strong>Engagement:</strong> three monthly member-update decks (Feb / Apr / May 2026) — see <a href="/engagement/meetings-decisions">Meetings &amp; decisions</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Technical:</strong>
          <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/04-governance-bodies/working-groups/technical/Smart Property Data Trust Framework Project Plan.md"><code>Smart Property Data Trust Framework Project Plan.md</code></a> — the live cross-WG plan.</li>
      </ul>
</Layout>
